<body>
    <h1>Task 19 - Technical Document</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"22090f70cf83" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-1.Intr=
oduction"><strong>1. Introduction</strong></h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"7e0ad37ec3b2" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-1.1Purpose"><s=
trong>1.1 Purpose</strong></h3>
<p local-id=3D"113142693aef">This document provides a comprehensive technic=
al overview of implementing a multi-channel email alerting system using Gra=
fana, designed to ensure reliable and scalable delivery of monitoring alert=
s across different email infrastructures.</p>
<p local-id=3D"8ecea50e0db6"><strong>The system integrates three distinct e=
mail delivery mechanisms:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"36c5e841bfa3">
<li local-id=3D"2651a0f26fc2">
<p local-id=3D"dc92201c5444">Self-hosted SMTP Mail Server (Postfix):<br>
Provides full control over email delivery, useful for internal systems and =
understanding SMTP fundamentals.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c7faf3898fae">
<p local-id=3D"41953f34feaa">AWS Simple Email Service (SES):<br>
A highly scalable, cost-effective cloud-based email service used for reliab=
le and bulk email delivery.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e8bf90b5ab89">
<p local-id=3D"caeddd58d5e8">AWS WorkMail:<br>
A managed enterprise email service that simulates real organizational email=
 systems with secure access and mailbox management.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e2a5b7be1e78"><strong>The purpose of this implementation is =
to:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"129a4012117d">
<li local-id=3D"b533339a9e36">
<p local-id=3D"51938aba47b1">Compare different email delivery architectures=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"81a41c60895b">
<p local-id=3D"83f75853be78">Ensure redundancy in alert delivery mechanisms=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"24b46d229d5a">
<p local-id=3D"16de27b2a994">Understand real-world alerting pipelines used =
in production environments</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"58f6df60c4a1"><strong>Target Audience:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"1a20ad735c06">
<li local-id=3D"f3091cfe2683">
<p local-id=3D"9632665e4212">DevOps Engineers</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b832b0f0e006">
<p local-id=3D"657539663d17">Site Reliability Engineers (SREs)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a531de1c285">
<p local-id=3D"ade8680485de">Cloud Architects</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0f71df407f35">
<p local-id=3D"54f5f7986c96">Monitoring and Operations Teams</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"4526af24ffe2">
<h3 local-id=3D"79be2345cd80" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-1.2Scope"><str=
ong>1.2 Scope</strong></h3>
<p local-id=3D"1f606c6061e4"><strong>This document covers the complete life=
cycle of setting up and validating a Grafana-based alerting system integrat=
ed with multiple email providers.</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"feb2b4fcad3e">The scope includes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"688a96d11dcf">
<li local-id=3D"287b10a505aa">
<p local-id=3D"b452d5f96cb2">Installation and configuration of a self-hoste=
d SMTP server (Postfix) on an EC2 instance</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"21a9a3737b82">
<p local-id=3D"67869ed464f6">Integration of Grafana with SMTP for sending a=
lert notifications</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6a62d95903f2">
<p local-id=3D"965245560215">Configuration of AWS SES, including:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ced950129a25">
<li local-id=3D"e6971d2b7345">
<p local-id=3D"ec7aa8546a9c">Email identity verification</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"059c0e7cf545">
<p local-id=3D"2ba37b7adb93">SMTP credentials</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"634126929d82">
<p local-id=3D"f53ea2547395">Implementation of AWS SNS as a notification in=
termediary</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"85bab3d2e2e1">
<p local-id=3D"858377076af1">Setup of AWS WorkMail, including:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5fae3f5fee34">
<li local-id=3D"8d78d3cb40f5">
<p local-id=3D"26ad00e2d1b5">Organization creation</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"02a6dc3bb623">
<p local-id=3D"5a1e77948694">User mailbox configuration</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"c0647c2ef832">
<p local-id=3D"43a343da1fe1">Integration of Grafana alerts with:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f9eea39a9ad3">
<li local-id=3D"e7e628d6b223">
<p local-id=3D"b25209700276">SMTP</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0cfb8270e650">
<p local-id=3D"34b2cfedba06">SES via SNS</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9325bdc9e705">
<p local-id=3D"92004879df96">WorkMail via SNS</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"d0406b97906e">
<p local-id=3D"4b0c0aa9bf46">End-to-end validation of alert delivery across=
 all channels</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f277139ea893">This implementation focuses on functional vali=
dation and architectural understanding, rather than production-grade automa=
tion.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"db0ac8566069">
<h2 local-id=3D"63467709e7ee" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-2.OverviewofDe=
vOpsProject"><strong>2. Overview of DevOps Project</strong></h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"ffa3a0818713" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-2.1Definition"=
><strong>2.1 Definition</strong></h3>
<p local-id=3D"0efe46c3bccc">This project demonstrates the design and imple=
mentation of a centralized monitoring and alerting pipeline, where system m=
etrics are collected, evaluated, and translated into actionable alerts deli=
vered via multiple communication channels.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3517d56ae706"><strong>The workflow consists of:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"f4c7f75b2bac">
<li local-id=3D"301a501d8c81">
<p local-id=3D"af35e1549482"><strong>Monitoring Layer (Prometheus):</strong=
><br>
Collects system metrics such as CPU usage, memory usage, and system availab=
ility.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b566b0d39f1f">
<p local-id=3D"27023ba2c311"><strong>Visualization &amp; Alerting Layer (Gr=
afana):</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"ecdb4b0262c9">
<li local-id=3D"6fcb8d843492">
<p local-id=3D"1c257dd97665">Visualizes metrics using dashboards</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"23db785c7634">
<p local-id=3D"37188e7845b5">Defines alert rules based on thresholds</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"1ace02ed4423">
<p local-id=3D"1baa2a40f169">Triggers alerts when conditions are met</p></l=
i>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"5ce1bfd6faa2">
<p local-id=3D"46a4fe91ec7e"><strong>Notification Layer:</strong><br>
Alerts are routed through:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ad40b9c54cba">
<li local-id=3D"383f7279e27d">
<p local-id=3D"5baa3c2425a3">SMTP (Postfix)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6a88cd68f8de">
<p local-id=3D"de3b967418d2">AWS SES</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cee96fb7a421">
<p local-id=3D"90b06f10e156">AWS WorkMail (via SNS)</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"9f47f0efd01c">This architecture reflects real-world DevOps s=
ystems where observability and alerting are critical for system reliability=
 and incident response.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"35aae963ea8f">
<h3 local-id=3D"53264f812f38" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-2.2KeyPrincipl=
es(AWSWell-ArchitectedFramework)"><strong>2.2 Key Principles (AWS Well-Arch=
itected Framework)</strong></h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"9cc7694c428f">
<li local-id=3D"f59171f0292f">
<p local-id=3D"4c0b3d531a71"><strong>Operational Excellence</strong></p></l=
i>
</ol>
<ul local-id=3D"1e4931f3b42d">
<li local-id=3D"cdc2d13c8f4a">
<p local-id=3D"214fd641eaed">Structured alerting pipeline with clearly defi=
ned components</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a43023dbb6ef">
<p local-id=3D"856e7100a5ed">Centralized monitoring using Grafana dashboard=
s</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4cf947fc7fe5">
<p local-id=3D"84ae204cbf69">Repeatable configuration across services</p></=
li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"2" local-id=3D"f4b31710a6a8">
<li local-id=3D"554c58f4ff4c">
<p local-id=3D"56cecdc6738a"><strong>Security</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<ul local-id=3D"c70105678323">
<li local-id=3D"975c5440f286">
<p local-id=3D"c4e45a748bb8">SMTP authentication enforced using credentials=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"04f50bee8663">
<p local-id=3D"4f7ad2d5f40a">TLS encryption enabled for secure email transm=
ission</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"40a6285f63c9">
<p local-id=3D"ba7597aba371">Verified identities in SES to prevent spoofing=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"98e7d2045440">
<p local-id=3D"ed0171f77688">Controlled access to WorkMail accounts</p></li=
>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"3" local-id=3D"1171333d9ad2">
<li local-id=3D"7406281e7e94">
<p local-id=3D"c3e9d7163a05"><strong>Reliability</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<ul local-id=3D"3bb2b850785b">
<li local-id=3D"ab46b9042dee">
<p local-id=3D"0a41754c58ef">Multiple email delivery mechanisms ensure redu=
ndancy</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1d4c81b0a0b8">
<p local-id=3D"b2be072c54f7">If one system fails (SMTP), others (SES/WorkMa=
il) can still deliver alerts</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d81c1d1a2c1f">
<p local-id=3D"22ade7ff7af8">SNS acts as a reliable message distribution la=
yer</p></li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"4" local-id=3D"63f65d55348f">
<li local-id=3D"ee8edbccfd88">
<p local-id=3D"d93531a1b02f"><strong>Performance Efficiency</strong></p></l=
i>
</ol>
<ul local-id=3D"f5667a745529">
<li local-id=3D"020a912f5625">
<p local-id=3D"766541c68c85">Low-latency alert delivery using optimized SMT=
P endpoints</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a40cfbb3810">
<p local-id=3D"7a9a1abdecf9">Efficient routing of notifications via SNS</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"2fb82161c54c">
<p local-id=3D"6c5ced311659">Lightweight infrastructure for fast response</=
p></li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"5" local-id=3D"972c599c081c">
<li local-id=3D"17c471c7e7c1">
<p local-id=3D"22440530f72c"><strong>Cost Optimization</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<ul local-id=3D"396ae659dd2f">
<li local-id=3D"29f12f6dac1e">
<p local-id=3D"4bfb8675c148">Use of AWS Free Tier (EC2, SES limits)</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"6bdbe7e496b4">
<p local-id=3D"f64bf58195bd">Minimal infrastructure footprint</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"640478e29d87">
<p local-id=3D"4f8e7879f2d3">Pay-as-you-go model for SES</p></li>
</ul>
<ol start=3D"6" local-id=3D"1e6553a17d41">
<li local-id=3D"994a95b5c8d2">
<p local-id=3D"0248616b4cc4"><strong>Sustainability</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<ul local-id=3D"dceeb61ba291">
<li local-id=3D"6a5da7a2e0b6">
<p local-id=3D"a0c5dd89953a">Efficient resource utilization</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"87b3b8708908">
<p local-id=3D"48bb71858cc0">Avoidance of unnecessary services</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4da6c4033281">
<p local-id=3D"c06f42b1d515">Minimal compute usage</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"a5612444132f">
<h3 local-id=3D"3f029e51e27f" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-2.3GoalsandObj=
ectives"><strong>2.3 Goals and Objectives</strong></h3>
<p local-id=3D"40c674edec16"><strong>The primary objectives of this project=
 are:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"0ddbf1525daa">
<li local-id=3D"dd54f06fbbe7">
<p local-id=3D"ee0602bf376b">To deploy and configure a self-hosted SMTP mai=
l server using Postfix</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"527e4114409a">
<p local-id=3D"4f80d20f9306">To integrate Grafana with SMTP for direct emai=
l alert delivery</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"19008880a0a3">
<p local-id=3D"e5f66d9e6b84">To configure AWS SES for scalable email delive=
ry</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a2e80daa07c2">
<p local-id=3D"23ce0e04f329">To set up AWS SNS topics and subscriptions for=
 notification routing</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3edc992850b9">
<p local-id=3D"5be4a3c8f36e">To configure AWS WorkMail for enterprise-grade=
 email handling</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"53032a2f2732">
<p local-id=3D"44389576c1ac">To implement a multi-channel alert delivery sy=
stem</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0fca0ffcb6de">
<p local-id=3D"2e858cf116e6">To validate successful alert delivery across a=
ll configured platforms</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c0b7f8d3dce9"><strong>Additionally, the project aims to prov=
ide a comparative understanding of:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"ffa986267356">
<li local-id=3D"9d8abc5ee740">
<p local-id=3D"70f53362fbfb">Traditional SMTP vs Cloud-based email services=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1c9c6dfde082">
<p local-id=3D"1a553579b475">Managed vs self-hosted solutions</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"fa224cde36be">
<h3 local-id=3D"770913fab06d" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-2.4Constraints=
andAssumptions"><strong>2.4 Constraints and Assumptions</strong></h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"84663ad11042" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-Constraints:">=
<strong>Constraints:</strong></h4>
<ul local-id=3D"1530a67b62bf">
<li local-id=3D"0c44be92633a">
<p local-id=3D"0d50d69452e0">Limited implementation time (4 hours)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"935f260cdeb5">
<p local-id=3D"fa9584ff5535">Use of AWS Free Tier resources</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"08bf080c381e">
<p local-id=3D"33854720197f">Manual configuration (no automation tools like=
 Terraform)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5b3cebd676e5">
<p local-id=3D"c3022a7c2d9b">Limited domain/email verification scope</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"84330ee7322c">
<h4 local-id=3D"590ee1c3774d" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-Assumptions:">=
<strong>Assumptions:</strong></h4>
<ul local-id=3D"fd42fb60a50d">
<li local-id=3D"857581274842">
<p local-id=3D"a4e71695607f">Stable internet connectivity is available</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"2f50d0625de5">
<p local-id=3D"fc5d27139ed3">Valid email credentials are used for SMTP auth=
entication</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d0bdae21def8">
<p local-id=3D"f6685fcd6d89">AWS account permissions allow SES, SNS, and Wo=
rkMail configuration</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4937e233de58">
<p local-id=3D"ed4c84c55b58">Security groups allow outbound SMTP traffic (p=
orts 587/465)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cd69583052f6">
<p local-id=3D"1431abc8d987">Grafana and Prometheus are already installed a=
nd running</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"2b03364133da">
<h2 local-id=3D"be81407541f8" id=3D"Task19-TechnicalDocument-3.Architecture=
